main event: An unidentified object was observed climbing to 30,000 feet over Marianna, Florida on December 6, 1955.
interesting points: The object reached an altitude of 30,000 feet in just 5 minutes., It was tracked by aircraft radar., The object was last reported over Maxwell AFB, Alabama., The weather during the observation included overcast skies with visibility of 12 miles., Conclusions indicated insufficient data for a clear identification; object could be a balloon or aircraft.
